body:
We also now provide an ES6 build to be picked by webpack2+/rollup for tree shaking 🎉 

* We agreed with @vvo on an export strategy:

```js
import instantsearch from 'instantsearch.js';
// provides same instantsearch object as es5 or <script> build
// useful for non-breaking changes on actual apps already using webpack or rollup

import { instantsearch } from 'instantsearch.js';
// provides instantsearch object without connectors and widgets attached.
// only `version` and `createQueryString` are available

import { connectXXX } from 'instantsearch.js'
// provides every available connectors

import { searchBox, menu, refinementList, ... } from 'instantsearch.js'
// provides every available widgets
```

* `.babelrc` file has now only environments, default one picked will be development

@vvo @bobylito 

Some more stats using the new ES6 build with `etch-instantsearch` which is only using the connectors API:

* before: `instantsearch.js: 438.42 KB`
* after: `instantsearch.js: 160.11 KB`

I reduced the size of the instantsearch.js dependency up to **~60%** !!

----

But in order to have this level of optimisation, I had to change the export strategy.

Importing `import main from './src/lib/main.js'` into `index.es6.js` will automatically require React and all the widgets. 

Even if on your side you import instantsearch.js this way: 
```js
import {instantsearch} from 'instantsearch.js'
```

----

In order to resolve this issue, the new exporting strategy now includes breaking changes:

```js
// throw an error when trying to access to `.connectors` or `.widgets`
import instantsearch from 'instantsearch.js';

instantsearch.connectors.connectMenu(...);
instantsearch.widgets.searchBox(...);

// does not throw
import {searchBox} from 'instantsearch.js/connectors';
import {connectMenu} from 'instantsearch.js/connectors';

connectMenu(...);
searchBox(...);
```

The error displayed is pretty dumb for now, will add link to the docs after I updated them in this PR:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/893837/27866084-57fd7ee2-6195-11e7-91c9-3ddd8073189d.png)

There is also something we did not think about with @vvo is the use-case of importing all the connectors by once which is not intuitive right now: 

```js
// require every connectors available
import * as connectors from 'instantsearch.js/dist-es6-module/src/connectors';
```

Something easier would be:

```js
import * as connectors from 'instantsearch.js/connectors';
import * as widgets from 'instantsearch.js/widgets';
```

I am not sure to get it but:

```js
import instantsearch from 'instantsearch.js';

instantsearch.connectors.connectMenu(...);
instantsearch.widgets.searchBox(...);
```

Should still work, otherwise it's a breaking change (and major version). If it does not work because we tried to have import {connectSearchBox} from 'instantsearch.js'; instead of having import {connectSearchBox} from 'instantsearch.js/connectors'; Then we should do the later instead (instantsearch.js/connectors).

```js
import * as connectors from 'instantsearch.js/connectors';
```

This should work for all envs but the use case may be edgy.

So to comply with a non-breaking changes update and we want the tree shaking to be working, we have to separate all the "main" modules this way:

```js
// instantsearchjs object without .connectors/.widgets property
import instantsearch from 'instantsearch.js/instantsearch';

import * as widgets from 'instantsearch.js/widgets';
import * as connectors from 'instantsearch.js/connectors';
```

This will imply documentation and won't work "out of the box" for existing projects, but it's non breaking and will provide really good results when you are not importing widgets or connectors.
